[32m+[m[32mA decision-making workspace where SBU teams submit tech-debt and improvement requests, AI scores them, and reviewers triage a capped, ranked queue that hands off to delivery.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## What this is[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mTwo ideas, one dataset:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m- A **submission** flow that turns rough asks into well-scored requests with effort estimates.[m
[32m+[m[32m- A **triage** flow that ranks those requests against a fixed capacity budget and a chronological set of timelines, so the work that gets approved is also the work that can actually fit.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## The two experiences[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mSwitch between them in the top-bar variant switcher — same data, different presentation:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m- **Signal** — a live ops console with a kanban-style triage board. Best when you think in columns and stages.[m
[32m+[m[32m- **Council** — a decision room with a single ranked queue, capacity bars, and an "approve / defer" rhythm. Best when you think in priorities.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## The three roles[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mUse the role switcher in the header to change perspective at any time:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m| Role | Where it lives | What it does |[m
[32m+[m[32m|---|---|---|[m
[32m+[m[32m| **Intake** (requestor) | Submission form | Submit a request. The Oracle/coach evaluates the justification as you type and suggests an effort estimate. |[m
[32m+[m[32m| **Triage** (reviewer) | The queue | Work the ranked list. Edit, defer, or approve & hand off. Capacity-by-timeline is always visible. |[m
[32m+[m[32m| **Review** (stakeholder) | Visibility view | Read-only window into decisions, capacity, and what's been handed off. |[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Day-to-day flow[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m1. **Submit** a request (manually or via import). It lands as `submitted`.[m
[32m+[m[32m2. **Auto-score** runs in the background and assigns a 0–100 total + confidence (high / medium / low) + per-pillar breakdown (impact, cost avoidance, scale, strategic alignment, feasibility).[m
[32m+[m[32m3. **Triage** the queue. Items ranked by AI score (or your manual rank, or by timeline). Filter by SBU, confidence, and timeline. Edit a request inline to re-trigger scoring. Approve to hand off (a fake `SXG-######` ID is generated), or defer.[m
[32m+[m[32m4. **Hand-off** items leave the queue and consume committed capacity.[m
[32m+[m[32m5. **Report** out: the Report button generates a PDF or PPTX of the current state.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Key concepts[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m- **Target timelines** are chronological: `FY27 Semester 1 — Sprint 1 → Sprint 2 → Sprint 3 → FY27 Semester 2 → Backlog`. Anywhere items are sorted by timeline, they follow this order.[m
[32m+[m[32m- **Capacity cut line.** There's a 200-day budget. As you walk the score-sorted queue, days accumulate; the line is drawn at the last item that still fits. Items below the line are visibly marked.[m
[32m+[m[32m- **Approved-but-future demotion.** If an item is approved for a timeline later than Sprint 1, it slips just below the cut line — it's already decided, it doesn't need to compete this sprint.[m
[32m+[m[32m- **Pending indicator.** Items that haven't been decided on yet (still `submitted` or `scored`) show a "pending" tag in the queue.[m
[32m+[m[32m- **Capacity by timeline** widget shows queue load per timeline (Sprint 1–3 and Sem 2 each have a 50-day bar; Backlog is uncapped). Handed-off and deferred items are excluded — you're looking at what's still open.[m
[32m+[m[32m- **Manual rank** lets a reviewer drag items into a preferred order, overriding AI score. Reset with the "AI rank" button.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Reports[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mClick **Report** in the header to export a snapshot of the current state as PDF or PowerPoint. Useful for stakeholder reviews and chamber-style decision meetings.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Tech, briefly[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m- React + Vite + TypeScript, TanStack Query, Tailwind, Framer Motion[m
[32m+[m[32m- Lovable Cloud backend (Supabase) with edge functions for: scoring (`score-request`), justification coaching (`coach-justification`), ranking explanations (`explain-ranking`), import (`import-requests`), seed (`seed-backlog`), reset (`reset-scenario`), and report build (`build-report`)[m
[32m+[m[32m- Edit and re-deploy through the Lovable project page; backend functions deploy automatically.[m
